The President of the United States issued a statement expressing support for the end of international supervision of Kosovo's independence. He commended Kosovo for making progress in building a modern, inclusive, and democratic state. The President emphasized that Kosovo's leaders must now take full responsibility for ensuring the principles of independence are realized for all citizens and encouraged them to engage with neighboring countries, particularly Serbia, to resolve outstanding issues. The President congratulated Kosovo on this milestone and its progress towards becoming a part of a peaceful Europe.